{"review_body": "I bought this product in Big Billion Day sale and I must say this is value for money which you are paying. In my society we get water which mix of river water + bore-well which is having TDS between 350 to 550, this purifier does the job well water test is awesome however I wont able to test the TDS after purification but you can drink the water as it tests like a normal water. I used to bring Bally 20 ltr water and suddenly we change to this water so not able to notice any difference in test. 

Before buying this water purifier I have done some online research and found that all costly purifier are only taking advantages of our fear and selling that overprice, yes the features are more but I guess you can buy this RO and take water in big container and boiled that and drink, if you so much worried about health my opinion no need to worry for so much and drink this water directly. 

The only imp think that you need to keep changing the filters as per instructions which make your water quality good over period of time.

Hope this will help and happy shopping.", "review_title": "Worth for Value", "website_path": "water_purifier", "product_title": "Pureit Advanced (RO + MF) 5 L Water Purifier"}

{"review_body": "I am writing it after a 2 weeks of use. I am a samsung lover. I started using this mobile and got to see that when the front flash is on to take the selfie, there will be a blur background once clicked. However selfie is perfect but I m worried if that is because of any internal camera issue. Not sure though. below are the Pros and Cons I observed.
Pros : 
1) Good Camera in daylight(both rear and front)
2) Good battery backup - Got a nice backup even with some high usage like games and Mobile data on for hours
3) Superb display even under the sunlight
4) Nice call quality
Cons:
1) Getting a cream blur color while clicking selfie with flash on
2) Bad camera under lowlight(selfies are worst wen there is a little light)
3) Expensive in the Galaxy ON series. Priced very high.
4) Bad RAM management. 
5) Not so fast even with Octacore processor(J7 2015 is better compared to it)

Not very satisfied with the speed. I am using J7 2015 and when compared to it, On8 fits nowhere. J7 is much more better and faster even with 1.5GB RAM and it is low cost too(J7 available now nearly for 13000).
